From: Thomas Graf <tgraf@suug.ch>
Date: Wed, 26 Nov 2014 13:42:18 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 188/349] net: Check for presence of IFLA_AF_SPEC

commit 4ea85e831e290cd967d161c66d0a3cf8be39f1f6 upstream.

ndo_bridge_setlink() is currently only called on the slave if
IFLA_AF_SPEC is set but this is a very fragile assumption and may
change in the future.

Cc: Ajit Khaparde <ajit.khaparde@emulex.com>
Cc: John Fastabend <john.r.fastabend@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Thomas Graf <tgraf@suug.ch>
Acked-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Signed-off-by: Liwei Song <liwei.song@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c   |    2 ++
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c |    2 ++
 2 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
index 28a65de..5f0e0c1 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/emulex/benet/be_main.c
@@ -3950,6 +3950,8 @@ static int be_ndo_bridge_setlink(struct net_device *dev,
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
 	br_spec = nlmsg_find_attr(nlh, sizeof(struct ifinfomsg), IFLA_AF_SPEC);
+	if (!br_spec)
+		return -EINVAL;
 
 	nla_for_each_nested(attr, br_spec, rem) {
 		if (nla_type(attr) != IFLA_BRIDGE_MODE)
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c
index 2328ef9..929aced 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c
@@ -7727,6 +7727,8 @@ static int ixgbe_ndo_bridge_setlink(struct net_device *dev,
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
 	br_spec = nlmsg_find_attr(nlh, sizeof(struct ifinfomsg), IFLA_AF_SPEC);
+	if (!br_spec)
+		return -EINVAL;
 
 	nla_for_each_nested(attr, br_spec, rem) {
 		__u16 mode;
